  <section class="suds-home-faq-section" id="faq">
    <div class="suds-home-shell">
      <div class="suds-home-section-title suds-home-section-title--center">
        <h2>Questions Before You Book</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="suds-home-faq">
        <details><summary>Which detail should I book?</summary><p>If your vehicle is already maintained, Basic may be enough. If it needs a proper inside-and-out reset, start with Signature. If it has heavier buildup, pet mess, rough paint, or resale prep needs, Elite is usually the better fit.</p></details>
        <details><summary>How much does mobile car detailing cost in Seattle?</summary><p>Mobile car detailing in Seattle starts with Basic, Signature, and Elite package pricing. Suds uses the live booking prices shown on the package cards, then adjusts only when vehicle size, heavy condition, pet hair, odor, or add-ons require more time.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Do you come to my house?</summary><p>Yes. Suds Auto Salon provides car detailing at home, offices, apartments, and approved service locations across the Seattle area when access and route timing work.</p></details>
        <details><summary>How long does a full detail take?</summary><p>A full mobile detail can take a few hours or most of the day depending on package, vehicle size, access, and condition. Basic is lighter, Signature fits most daily drivers, and Elite reserves more time for heavier buildup.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Do you remove pet hair?</summary><p>Yes. Suds can clean pet hair from seats, carpets, mats, and cargo areas. Heavy embedded pet hair may require extra time or a pet hair add-on so the appointment is priced and scheduled correctly.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Can you get coffee, vomit, grease, or other stains out of car seats?</summary><p>Stain extraction can improve many spills and normal buildup, but results depend on the material, age, and severity. Severe stains, biological messes, or grease-heavy areas should be quoted before the appointment.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Do you offer ceramic coating in Seattle?</summary><p>Yes. Ceramic coating is available for Seattle-area drivers who want longer-lasting gloss, slickness, and easier maintenance than wax. The vehicle needs proper cleaning and prep before coating.</p></details>
        <details><summary>What's the difference between a car wash and a detail?</summary><p>A car wash mainly cleans the exterior surface. A detail goes deeper into interior grime, touchpoints, carpets, wheels, road film, paint contamination, and finish care.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Do you need access to water or power?</summary><p>Water and power needs can depend on the service and appointment location. Share your address or location details when booking so Sam can confirm what is needed.</p></details>
        <details><summary>What happens if it rains?</summary><p>Seattle weather is part of mobile detailing. Light rain does not always stop an appointment, but severe weather, unsafe conditions, or lack of covered access may require rescheduling.</p></details>
        <details><summary>How often should I detail my car in the Pacific Northwest?</summary><p>Most Seattle-area vehicles benefit from a reset a few times per year, with maintenance every month or two if the vehicle sees commuting, kids, pets, outdoor parking, or frequent rain grime.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Do you detail Teslas and EVs?</summary><p>Yes. Suds details Teslas, EVs, hybrids, daily drivers, SUVs, trucks, and family vehicles. The package still depends on size, condition, and the result you want.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Do you offer a monthly maintenance plan?</summary><p>Yes. Maintenance detailing is available after an initial reset for drivers who want priority upkeep and a cleaner vehicle without starting over every few months.</p></details>
        <details><summary>How do I book?</summary><p>Use the Book My Detail button to choose a package and schedule. If you are unsure, request a quote or text photos for a package recommendation first.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Are you licensed and insured?</summary><p>Suds Auto Salon is a licensed Washington LLC. If you need current insurance details for an apartment, office, or commercial location, ask before booking.</p></details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {%- if has_gallery_blocks or request.design_mode -%}
    <section class="suds-home-results suds-home-results--bottom" id="real-photo-proof">
      <div class="suds-home-shell">
        <div class="suds-home-section-title suds-home-section-title--center">
          <h2>Real Suds Photo Proof</h2>
          <p>Recent Suds Auto Salon details, from specialty vehicles to interior resets, exterior gloss, wheels, and family vehicle cleanup.</p>
        </div>

        {%- if has_gallery_blocks -%}
